{"name": "kafka-slurm-agent", "metadata": {"name": "kafka-slurm-agent", "version": "1.3.3", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/prubach/kafka-slurm-agent", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["simple-slurm", "kafka-python-ng", "psutil", "python-math", "faust-streaming", "werkzeug", "wrapt-timeout-decorator"], "summary": "The Kafka Slurm Agent is a distributed computing and stream processing engine that can be used to run python code acrossmultiple SLURM managed HPC clusters or individual workstations.It uses Kafka to asynchronously communicate with agents installed on clusters and workstations.It contains a monitoring tool with a Web JSON API and a job submitter.It is a pure Python implementation using faust stream processing", "upload_time": 1732211556}, "documentation": ["# Kafka Slurm Agent\n\nThe Kafka Slurm Agent is a distributed computing and stream processing engine \nthat can be used to run python code across multiple **SLURM** managed HPC clusters or individual workstations.\nIt uses Kafka to asynchronously communicate with agents installed on clusters and workstations.\nIt contains a monitoring tool with a Web JSON API and a job submitter.\nIt is a pure Python implementation using faust stream processing\n\n## Installation.\n\nUse the standard ``pip`` tool to install. The recommended way is to use a Python virtual environment:\n``python3 -m venv venv``\n``source venv/bin/activate``\n``pip install kafka-slurm-agent``\n\n## Quick User Guide\n\n### Create a new project\n\nIn the folder in which you created the ``venv`` subfolder run the following command:\n``kafka-slurm create-project --folder .``\nThis will generate the following files:\n   1. ``kafkaslurm_cfg.py`` - the configuration file\n   2. Startup scripts for **worker-agent**, **cluster-agent** and **monitor-agent**\n   3. An example file to run your code (``run.py``)\n   4. The job submitter example (``submitter.py``)\n   5. The class that can be optionally used to override the existing implementation of the **worker-agent** (``my_worker_agent.py`)\n\n### Configuration\nPlease adjust the config file.\n1. Modify the configuration of the connection to **Apache Kafka**. The default one assumes that kafka is running on *localhost* and default port (*9092*) and doesn't use authentication or SSL.\n     In the comments you will find parameters necessary to connect to **Kafka** configured using SASL and plaintext password. If you use this type of connection please uncomment also the line that starts with:\n`` # KAFKA_FAUST_BROKER_CREDENTIALS``\n2. Make sure that ``PREFIX` points to the location of your project\n3. Change the names of topics used for your project to avoid any conflict with projects sharing the same kafka instance.\n4. If you want to use a SLURM cluster please change the job ``CLUSTER_JOB_NAME_SUFFIX = '_KSA'`` to avoid conflicts with other projects running on your slurm cluster. The jobs managed by **cluster-agent** will be named *\"JOBID_SUFFIX\"* where the JOBID is the identifier that you assign when submitting a job and SUFFIX is handled by this configuration parameter.\n\nFor a full list of configuration parameters refer to the documentation.\n\n### Creating topics on Kafka with appropriate partitions\n\nUse the built-in command ``kafka-slurm`` to create topics. You should set the ``--new-topic-partitions`` paramter to at least the number of planned clusters and workstations that will be used simultaneously.\nFor example: \n``kafka-slurm --new-topic-partitions 4 topics-create``\n\n### Implement your code\n\nAn example of a script that you can implement is generated in ``run.py``\n\n## Submitting jobs\n\nOnce this is ready, you can test your project locally:\n1. Open a new terminal and start the **worker-agent** (``./start_worker_agent``)\n2. Open a new terminal and start the **monitor-agent** (``./start_monitor_agent``)\n3. Submit new jobs using the ``submitter.py``\n\nYou can monitor the execution by opening http://localhost:6067/mon/stats/ on the host on which you've started the **monitor-agent**.\n\n## Demo project\n\nYou can download and directly run a demonstration project: https://github.com/ilbsm/ksa_demo \n"], "modules": [{"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.run_cluster_agent_check", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.process", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "stream", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.check_statuses", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "app", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.send_heartbeat", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "app", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.get_jobs", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "web", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.get_stat", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "web", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.get_stat", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "web", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.app", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.jobs_topic", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.job_status", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.thread_pool", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.ca_class", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.ca", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.heartbeat_sender", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.worker_agent.current_jobs", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.process_jobs", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "stream", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["stats_thread_pool = ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=1)"]}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.get_stats_done", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "web", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.get_stats", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "web", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.get_stats", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "web", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "input_job_id", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.get_stat", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "web", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.get_new", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.get_monitor_processed", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.app", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.jobs_topic", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.done_topic", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.error_topic", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.new_topic", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.heartbeat_topic", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.monitor_agent.job_status", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.command", "documentation": ["source   jcollado http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1191374/subprocess-with-timeout?rq=1"], "functions": [{"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.command.kill", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "proc_pid", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.command.command", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.command.Command", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "kafka_slurm_agent.command.Command.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cmd", "type": null, "defaul